The Chronicle Angela Sibanda, Chronicle Reporter Three people died on the spot while two others were hospitalised with serious injuries in Bulawayo after a VW Golf car hit a tree near the 12 Avenue and Samuel Parirenyatwa Road intersection in the wee hours of Wednesday. <img class="alignnone wp-image-591026 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/02/Accident-12.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/02/Accident-12.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/02/Accident-12-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The accident happened at 2am. The driver is believed to have lost control of his car. <img class="alignnone wp-image-591021 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/02/Accident-14.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/02/Accident-14.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/02/Accident-14-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> @angelasibanda18    